sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260425T183959Za_1777168754.log:252:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T02:01:00.496Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777168860496_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-018 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260425T183959Za_1777168754.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/midi_keyboard_listener.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/theramini_listener.py`\n- `tests/test_phrase_tracker.py`\n- `tests/test_midi_keyboard_listener_runtime.py`\n- `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly tracks continuous play duration and emits `phrase_started` and `phrase_ended` events when the 5-second threshold is crossed. Logic is encapsulated in a reusable `PhraseTracker` class.\n\n## Completeness\nBoth MIDI keyboard and Theramini listeners have been integrated with the `PhraseTracker`. The 5-second threshold is used as specified. Unit tests cover both the core logic and the integration in both listeners.\n\n## Consistency\nThe changes follow existing patterns in the codebase for listener state updates and event emission. The use of a standard `senseweave` module for the tracker is consistent with the architectural layout.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were identified. The implementation uses standard library features and does not introduce external dependencies.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and documented. The tests are comprehensive, covering edge cases like short bursts, resets, and idle-tone overrides in the Theramini listener.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] Pre-existing mypy errors in `theramini_listener.py` and `audio_analysis.py` were observed but are unrelated to this task. One mypy error in the existing test suite was fixed during verification to improve clarity.\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] Environmental constraints (macOS Seatbelt) cause some unrelated tests in the full suite to fail due to permission/caching issues, but T-018 specific tests pass 100%.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The `PhraseTracker` is a good abstraction that can be reused for other input sources if needed.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-018@20260425t183959za-verify.md"}}
